race.comment: PRIDE OF JEZZA (2) doesn't win often but is a model of consistency, boasting a strong record at his home track. From a good gate and reunited with McDougall, he looks the one they'll have to beat. SAWMILL (3) resumes after breaking her maiden impressively at Moruya, rattling home as favourite. Draws the inside and maps to get the gun run. Big threat. IN THE NIC OF TIME (1) closed off well into fourth when resuming at Gundagai and will appreciate the rise in trip. Sure to have tightened up and is right in the mix. GUSTAV (6) hasn't broken through this campaign but continues to race well. With a fitness edge, he should make his presence felt. SNATCHED (7) looks best of the rest.
